Intro to docker compose ?

Docker compose allows you have multi container orchestration 
- Multiple docker containers can be spun up the same time in a single command 
- with the docker compose yaml file

- Docker compose auto creates a network for your containers - before you need custom individual networks 
- Containers & services can now easily communicate with each other 

Docker compose down = stops all running containers 
Docker compose build = rebuilds your containers 
Docker compose up -d = spins up multiple containers 

? Why is docker compose important in devops 

- Makes testing & development easier - quickly spinning up environments and services - one command to spin up instead of manual 
- Useful of testing as it replicates the production environment locally for testing 
- Ensures consistancy - everyone working in the same environment due to establishing that in the yaml file 
- Enhances teamwork - easier to version control and share between colleagues - working in the same set up 


? What are docker registries 
- Storage and distribution system for docker images - like an online library of images 
- Build them -> push to registry 
- Pull image when you need them 

Public registries -> Docker hub 
Private registries -> AWS ECR -> internal images secure an only u can control access

? Why are registries important 
- Streamline deployment - easily stored so they can be easily deployed across multiple environments ( from development to production ) 
- Enhance collaboration - share and manage efficiency 
- Ensure consistency - making sure exact image is being using for testing and development  
